The Eindhoven University of Technology (TU/e) has the=20
following vacancy:=20
=A0
One PhD position on the project
"Efficient Multi-Core Model Checking" (V50.122)=20
=A0
Project description=20
=A0=20
Model checking is one of the most successful formal=20
techniques for automated analysis and finding errors in=20
software and hardware. Nowadays, model checking is used by=20
major companies, like Microsoft and Intel, to improve the=20
quality of their products.=20
=A0=A0=20
The aim of this project is to develop algorithms for model=20
checking (including probabilistic model checking) that can=20
fully exploit the parallelism of the new generations of=20
multi- and many-core processors. The main bottleneck in=20
practical applications of model checking is the state=20
space explosion that has impact on the required memory and=20
run-time. Therefore, we will strive towards designing=20
efficient algorithms that are compatible with the major
techniques for state space reduction, like partial-order or=20
symmetry reduction.=20
=A0
We intend to develop prototype implementations of the new=20
algorithms In model checkers, like Spin and its=20
extensions, as well as the probabilistic model checker=20
MRMC. The prototype implementations will be validated on=20
case studies including models of biological systems.=20
=A0=A0=20
As PhD Student, you will:=20
=A0=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0 * perform scientific research;=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0 * work on the implementation of (prototype) tools;=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0 * present results at international conferences;=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0 * publish results in conference proceedings and=20
scientific journals;=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0 * write a Ph.D. thesis;=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0 * participate in activities of the group and of the=20
department.=20
=A0=20
=A0=20
Requirements=20
=A0=20
We are looking for a candidate who meets the following=20
requirements:=20
=A0=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0 * a MSc degree in Computer Science or equivalent;=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0 * a solid theoretical background (preferably in model=20
checking or=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 other formal methods);=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0 * interest and experience in programming (especially=20
experience in parallel and/or distributed computing will=20
be considered an advantage);=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0 * good communication- and writing skills in English.=20
=A0=20
=A0=20
Working Environment, Appointment and Salary=20
=A0
The project will be implemented as cooperation of several=20
departments and groups. The Software Engineering and=20
Technology group, headed by prof. dr. Mark van den Brand=20
at the M&CS department of TU/e, focuses on maintaining=20
consistency between models and code. Also, part of the=20
work within the project will be done in the group of prof.=20
dr. Joost-Pieter Katoen at RWTH Aachen University. Prof.=20
Katoen has internationally recognized competence in the=20
field of formal specification and verification of=20
probabilistic systems. Biologically inspired case=20
studies will be provided by the Biomodeling and=20
Bioinformatics group of prof. dr. Peter Hilbers, who is=20
also an expert on parallel algorithms and has an=20
outstanding record in applications of parallel computing=20
in biology. Most of the tool implementations will be done=20
in close collaboration with the Laboratory for Quality=20
Software at the M&CS at TU/e.=20
=A0
We offer:=20
=A0=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0 * a full-time employment for 4 years with an=20
intermediate evaluation=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 after 1 year;=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0 * a stimulating scientific environment with=20
international cooperation=20
=A0
=A0=A0=A0=A0 * access to modern equipment (multi- and many-core=20
systems, computer clusters)=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0 * a salary of Euro 2,042 per month (gross) in the=20
first year,=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 increasing to Euro 2,612 per month (gross) in the=20
fourth year.=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 Moreover 8% holiday allowance and 8.3 % End-of-year=20
bonus is=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 provided annually;=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0 * Support with your personal development and career=20
planning;=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0 * Attractive secondary labour conditions (including=20
excellent work facilities, child care, sports facilities).=20
=A0=20
Information=20
=A0=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0 * Information about the position:=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 dr. Dragan Bosnacki=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 (dragan@win.tue.nl),=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 or=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 prof. dr. Mark van den Brand=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 (M.G.J.v.d.Brand@tue.nl),=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 prof. dr. Joost-Pieter Katoen=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 (katoen@cs.rwth-aachen.de),=20
=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 prof. dr. Peter Hilbers (P.A.J.Hilbers@tue.nl).
=A0
=A0=A0=A0=A0 * Information about the job conditions:=20
Mrs. Y.Bloemers-Kluijtmans, HR advisor (pzbmt@tue.nl)=A0=20
